<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB"
                    xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Uninstallation</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p><ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> ships with uninstallers for automatically uninstalling the <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> software components. </p>
            <p>Before uninstalling, it is recommended that you make a backup of the configuration files, log files, and the data created during operation. For details on backups, refer to <xref
                    href="../../shared/operationmaintenance/c-backup.xml"/>.</p>
            <p>When uninstalling the <ph
                            conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> software components, stick to the following sequence: </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Uninstall the agents. </li>
                    <li>Uninstall the Monitoring Service and the OpenStack extensions.</li>
                    <li>Manually remove remaining <ph conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> components if they are no longer required.</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
